1.title: Pilot
1.plot: Rick hires his old friends to come work for him as he begins a new business venture, a fish and chips restaurant called "The Codfather". He picks up his most incompetent friend, Franco, from the airport and proceeds to buy him a van and a bakery with the hopes of giving Franco a fresh start.

2.title: Franco Bakery
2.plot: As Rick brings his nephew Joey to help out with 'The Codfather', Rob must deal with him while also trying to help out the dysfunctional Franco, who is trying to open 'Franco Bakery'

3.title: The Conference
3.plot: After Rick opens his 100th location, he calls a franchisee meeting to announce that he will be stepping down from presidency and announces who will take his place.

4.title: Mr. President
4.plot: Rob's first week as President is a disaster. He takes Friday off to plan a corporate Golf Tournament, which coincidentally is on his birthday. Franco begins his baker's training.

5.title: Golf, Anyone?
5.plot: Rick and Rob head to Banff to celebrate Rick's birthday, meanwhile Billy is back at the office continuing his romantic pursuit of Sabrina.

6.title: Franco's Downfall
6.plot: The WingMen take a trip to Winnipeg for Johnny Hendrix's UFC fight with Sabrina, Faith and Johnny Hendrix himself. We learn that Sabrina and Rob have been having an affair and Franco reveals that he has a crush on Faith.

7.title: Vivek Pizza
7.plot: After Rick comes to the conclusion that he does not believe Franco can successfully run a bakery, Franco is forced to find other work. He begins working as a Pizza Delivery Boy for an eccentric pizza connoisseur.

8.title: Mayor Duffy
8.plot: The WingMen get political and visit their friend, Mayor Duffy in Brechin. Franco makes the mistake of attempting to open the bakery before acquiring a Business license.

9.title: Lost Wages, Nevada
9.plot: The time has come for Rob Stewart's annual Golf Tournament, unfortunately a big rainstorm is right on the horizon. Meanwhile things are up with Rick, Faith and Rachelle in Las Vegas.

10.title: Franco, Vegas
10.plot: The WingMen and crew deal with the fallout of both the Vegas Trip and Rob Stewart's Annual Golf Tournament. Rick gives Franco another chance by offering him the job of managing the Codfather.

11.title: The Pig Roast
11.plot: Billy is looking for love, he goes on a series of back-to-back blind dates at the local espresso café. Meanwhile Rob Stewart and Franco assess the viability of Franco Bakery.

12.title: Miss America
12.plot: Rick takes Mild Ricky out to Los Angeles for his birthday where they have a run in with a Miss American contestant. Meanwhile Franco is in Halifax where he decides to give online dating a try.

13.title: The Codfather
13.plot: While the Codfather's seems to be going down in flames, tensions reach a breaking point between Rob Stewart and Rick.

locations: Banff, Banff National Park, Alberta, Canada
New York City, New York, USA
imdb.plot outline: The show follows the incredible true-life story of Rick, aka "THE WINGMAN," a successful purveyor of chicken wings, who turned $100 into a 100 store chicken wing chain, only to lose it all to his staff of misfits. In the first episode, he announces a significant milestone, the opening of his 100th chicken wing restaurant. With the same breath and consistent with his 'Wild' nature, he then decides to tell his franchisees that he will be shifting gears and playing himself in a fictitious mockumentary for a change of pace. The show was influenced by the incredible events surrounding his personal life.
imdb.title: WingMen
plot: The show follows the incredible true-life story of Rick, aka "THE WINGMAN," a successful purveyor of chicken wings, who turned $100 into a 100 store chicken wing chain, only to lose it all to his staff of misfits. In the first episode, he announces a significant milestone, the opening of his 100th chicken wing restaurant. With the same breath and consistent with his 'Wild' nature, he then decides to tell his franchisees that he will be shifting gears and playing himself in a fictitious mockumentary for a change of pace. The show was influenced by the incredible events surrounding his personal life.

Rooted in the present day this digitally remastered docuseries takes place mostly in reality extenuated by fantastic flashbacks, delusion flash forwards and cartoonish side characters. _WingMen_ (qv) is a mix of comedy and drama employing a various style of shooting disciplines such as interviews, talking into the camera, funny interstitials and fly on the wall techniques.
